Seventh Grade Orientation will be held on Wednesday, September 2nd.

🔹Students with last names A-K will be 8:45 to 10:15 am.

🔹Students with last names L-Z will be 10:30 am to 12:00 pm.

Students will meet on the grass between the high school parking lot and the playground, weather permitting.

🔹Bring a mask, they are required.

High School Principal, Mr. Hexum, will have Zoom meetings with parents at noon and 7:00 pm on Wednesday, September 2nd.

Welcome to 7th grade! Your teachers look forward to meeting you! #GoEsko

Since we weren’t able to hold our annual Kindergarten Round-up event last March, we have rescheduled the event for Wednesday, August 19 at 6:00 pm.

We are inviting our new Kindergarten students and their families (no siblings) to gather in the grassy area of our playground behind Winterqiust Elementary. Please bring a lawn chair.

We will share information regarding your child’s Kindergarten experience, answer any questions you might have and allow your child to spend time with their class and teacher. It will be great to gather as a school community!

#GoEsko

post_text:
Do you love to write? Are you looking for a chance to connect with other student writers and hone your skills?

Check out Michigan Tech’s virtual Calling All Writers! course -- a week-long writing workshop delivered by professors in their Department of Humanities.

Using interactive games and activities, you’ll explore writing in a variety of forms, meet current Michigan Tech students, engage with professional writers, and discover writing-related careers. You’ll also produce your own writing projects (and even get help finding places to submit them for publication!).

The course runs July 13-17, 2020 and registration is now open. To maintain small instructor ratios and high-quality engagement, seats are very limited. Please visit the Course Catalog for more information and to apply.

Center for Educational Outreach
Michigan Technological University
(906) 487-2219 | syp.mtu.edu

#GoEsko

Minnesota is now offering funds for families of children ages 5 to 18 who qualify for free or reduced-price school meals.

The new program, called Pandemic EBT (P-EBT), will provide up to $325 per child that families can use to purchase nutritious food for their household. Approximately 350,000 Minnesota children could benefit.

Learn more at http://www.mn.p-ebt.org/.

#GoEsko

post_text:
We are proud to announce that Esko HS has been selected as a recipient of the 2020 Riding for Focus Grant from @outride!

We could not be more excited about this opportunity to get more kids on bikes and bring a cycling program to our high school physical education classes. Learn more through through these tags- #ridingforfocus #morekidsonbikes #whatwillyououtride or check out this link- outridebike.org.

You can expect to see our students on brand new specialized mountain bikes this fall. The Riding for Focus Grant is a combination of cycling, fitness, academic performance, all while instilling a lifelong passion for cycling.

The program is based on research from Stanford Medical School and how cycling can positively alter brain activity with increased attention span, boosted moods, and improved fitness.

Way to go Sue, Sarah and George in earning this grant and building lifelong activities for our students! #GoEsko

post_text:
This fall the Carlton County Soil and Water Conservation District approached the school about a project to engage students in learning about what the SWCD does in the local community.

They invited about a dozen students on a field trip to visit a local project of theirs on the Midway River and challenged the students to create an informative video about the role that SWCD plays in local communities around the state.

In February the SWCD selected the top videos for recognition. Sophomores Lexi Tester and Jack McWilliams teamed up to produce the winning video and received a $100 prize along with coveted SWCD t-shirts. SWCD hosted an awards luncheon at Eskimo Pizza Pies to honor the participants and winners.

To check out the project and the winning videos visit the SWCD site at https://carltonswcd.org.

Way to go Michael, Lexi, Jack, Emily, and Audrey! #GoEsko

Students in French 2 used « old school » manipulatives to practice replacing direct object pronouns.

They had to choose which pronoun to use and then put it in the correct spot in the sentence.

Past participles have to agree in gender and number. If you don't understand this in English, imagine being able to do this in French!

#soproud #GoEsko

post_text:
Happy Friday morning to you all, #GoEsko family!

This morning we are excited for you to get to know our very own 6th grade teacher Mrs. Johnson a little bit better. Feel free to give her a shout out in the comments below!

"Hi! My name is Sara Johnson and I taught in St. Paul for 2 years before making the move back to the Northland in 2011 to teach 6th grade here in Esko.

I graduated high school from Duluth East and received a BA in Education from Concordia College in Moorhead, MN. I am passionate about teaching and am lucky to be working in such a wonderful school!

I reside in Duluth where I live with my husband and son. I enjoy spending time with my family, running, and being outdoors when I am not teaching."

Esko fifth graders spent February 19-21 up at Wolf Ridge Environmental Learning Center.

Students ventured out on the ropes course, took a four mile snowshoe hike, climbed the rock wall, learned some beginning orienteering skills, and studied mammals and animal signs.

What a fun and educational time! #GoEsko

post_text:
"I Love to Read Month" fun!

Last week, Mrs. Baird's 1st graders teamed up with the afternoon 4-year-old school readiness class for I Love To Read Month.

They each got a buddy and the preschooler got to pick some books for the first grader to read aloud to them. It’s amazing to see the growth that happens between these two years! The preschool teachers had many of these kids just two years ago and Mrs. Baird got to meet students that may be with her in just two short years!

It was a fun experience for everyone!
#ILovetoReadMonth #GoEsko
